						               													<description>Duel Trading Card Game is a realtime online card game where players assume the role of a powerful mage, casting spells and abilities trying to reduce their opponents HP to 0 to win the duel. There are no creatures or items allowed in the Tournament of Gods, so player&amp;rsquo;s decks that they build consist entirely of spells and abilities. Duel is realtime, meaning there are no turns and both players receive 1 Mana every 5 seconds to use to draw cards and cast spells and abilities.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Cast a spell by spending the amount of Mana listed as a gold number in the top right of the card and set the projectile sideways on one of the Spell Timers in the center of the field. Set it facing your opponents, as if it was in the air on its way to hit them. Your opponent then has 10 seconds to hit that incoming attack with one of their own, (and if the one that they use is double the ATK or more of the one it collided with it not only kills the weaker one but also continues on towards the enemy&amp;rsquo;s HP.) or use a quick-play ability such as Blink or Reflect.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players make decks of 50 cards that have no other restrictions whatsoever, just a 50 card max, but they do also have something called a Type Mastery, which is a single type (card color) that they can cast for 1 less Mana and take one less Damage from. There&amp;rsquo;s no limit to how many spells can be used against a single incoming attack, and there&amp;rsquo;s no limit on how many can be played per turn, or how many cards players can draw per turn either, the only limit is how much Mana you have.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
